<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><Document xmlns="http://www.ortodokskoptik.id/BukuBacaanKoptik">   <Season id="Resurrection">      <Section expanded="true">                     <Title>            <Language id="English">The Enactment of the Glorious Resurrection</Language>                                                   </Title>                  <Role id="Deacon">            <Comment>               <Language id="English">                  The enactment of the Resurrection represents a "scene" that takes place in front of Paradise: two angels stand at the gate of paradise and call to the angel who is guarding it announcing the resurrection of the Lord; “the angels then commands that the gates of Paradise be lifted that the King of glory may enter" (Psalm 23).                  <ol>                     <li>The veil of the sanctuary is closed and the lights in the church are all turned off.</li>                     <li>A deacon carries the Icon of the Resurrection and stands outside the veil of the Sanctuary.</li>                     <li>The enactment begins with two deacons and priest alternating with the following:</li>                  </ol>               </Language>            </Comment>                        <Text>               <Language id="Coptic">                  &lt;rictoc a~nect/               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Christ is risen               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  المسيح قام               </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Priest">            <Text>               <Language id="Coptic">                  Al/youc a~nect/               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Truly He is risen               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  بالحقيقة قد قام                </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Deacon">            <Text>               <Language id="Coptic">                  &lt;rictoc a~nect/               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Christ is risen               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  المسيح قام               </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Priest">            <Text>               <Language id="Coptic">                  Al/youc a~nect/               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Truly He is risen               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  بالحقيقة قد قام               </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Deacon">            <Text>               <Language id="Coptic">                  &lt;rictoc a~nect/               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Christ is risen               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  المسيح قام               </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Priest">            <Text>               <Language id="Coptic">                  Al/youc a~nect/               </Language>               <Language id="English">                  Truly He is risen               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  بالحقيقة قد قام               </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Deacon">            <Text>                                       <Language id="English">                  Lift up your gates, O rulers! And be raised up, O eternal gates!,               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  افتحوا ايها الملوك ابوابكم وارتفعي ايتها الأبواب الدهرية ،               </Language>                     </Text>                        <Text>                                       <Language id="English">                  ...that the King of glory may enter.               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  ...ليدخل ملك المجد.               </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Priest">            <Text>                                       <Language id="English">                  Who is the King of Glory?               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  مَن هو ملك المجد؟               </Language>                     </Text>         </Role>                  <Role id="Deacon">            <Text>                                       <Language id="English">                  The Lord, the powerful, the strong, the mighty, victorious in battles; He is the King of glory.               </Language>               <Language id="Arabic">                  الرب العزيز القوي الجبّار القاهر قي الحروب هو ملك المجد.               </Language>                     </Text>            <Comment>               <Language id="English">                  <ol start="4">                     <li>The deacon knocks on the gate of the sanctuary and the veil is opened.</li>                     <li>The lights are turned on and the deacons cry out with the hymn of the Resurrection "Christ is Risen (<span class="Coptic">&lt;rictoc a~nect/</span>)":</li>                  </ol>               </Language>            </Comment>         </Role>      </Section>   </Season></Document>